    <text id="A3021T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Tony writes Annie relating his troubles during a winter march and his hope to
                    return home.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="-05-16">May 16th</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Annie,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p> I take the privilege of writing you a few lines this morning as I am going up to
                    the mountain <orig reg="today">to day</orig>. I have not heard from you for some
                    time &amp; have come to the conclusion that you have forgotten me but I hope
                        <del hand="h1">you</del>this is a mistake I have seen hard times since I
                        <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> last wrote you. we had a hard march the other day to
                    Shepards Town about twelve miles from this place. we were in a terrible hail
                    storm. I thought we would certainly be killed. but an <orig reg="overruling"
                        >over ruling</orig> providence was over us. I had the pleasure of meeting
                        <abbr expan="Doctor">D<hi rend="super">r.</hi></abbr> Baggs last evening at
                    twilight I was very much surprised &amp; agreeably <unclear>too</unclear>.
                    Sam is here but I have not <pb n="2"/>seen him yet.</p>
                <p> I wish I had time to write you a long letter but I must stop for the present.
                    may heaven bless <hi rend="underline">you.</hi> &amp; may <hi
                        rend="underline">I</hi> be permitted to <unclear>return</unclear> again and
                    have the pleasure of seeing once more <hi rend="underline">the</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">object</hi> of my affections. <abbr expan="Lieutenant"
                        >Lieut.</abbr> Mc<unclear>Harry</unclear> is going home this morning on a
                    furlough. If you want to hear all about the <unclear>Ferry</unclear> just go
                    over to his house as soon as you get this &amp; you'll <orig reg="hear"
                        >heare</orig> all.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours in haste</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Tony Pastor</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
